quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,Of what do they question one another
  78,2,About the Great News
  78,3,About which they are in disagreement
  78,4,"Verily, they shall soon come to know"
  78,5,"Verily, verily, they shall soon come to know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth an expanse
  78,7,And the mountains as projections (thereon)
  78,8,And created you in pairs
  78,9,And made your sleep for rest
  78,10,And made the night to be a covering
  78,11,And made the day for livelihood and activity
  78,12,And made above you seven firmaments (heavens)
  78,13,And placed therein a shining lamp (the Sun)
  78,14,And do We not send down from the clouds water in abundance
  78,15,That We may bring forth thereby corn and vegetable
  78,16,And gardens dense and luxuriant
  78,17,Surely the Day of Decision (or Sorting ) is a thing appointed
  78,18,The day on which the trumpet shall be blown so you shall come forth in hosts
  78,19,And the heaven shall be opened as if it were all doors
  78,20,And the mountains shall be moved off so that they shall remain a mere semblance
  78,21,Surely hell lies in ambush
  78,22,A destination for those who transgress the bounds
  78,23,Abiding therein for ages
  78,24,They shall not taste therein anything cool nor drink
  78,25,But boiling and intensely cold water
  78,26,Requital corresponding (or proportional to their state)
  78,27,Surely they feared not the account
  78,28,And called Our revelations a lie with strong denial
  78,29,And We have preserved all things in a Record
  78,30,So taste you (the fruits of your deeds)! For We will not add to you aught but torment
  78,31,"Surely for the righteous is achievement (or success, self-fulfilment)"
  78,32,Gardens and vineyards
  78,33,"And those showing freshness of youth, equals in age"
  78,34,And a pure cup
  78,35,They shall not hear therein any vain words nor lying
  78,36,"A reward from your Lord, a gift according to reckoning (or sufficient)"
  78,37,"From the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between them, the Beneficent Allah, with whom none can argue"
  78,38,The day on which the Spirit and the angels shall stand arrayed; they speak not except him whom the Beneficent permits and who speaks aright
  78,39,"That is the Day of Certain Reality, so whoever desires may take refuge with his Lord"
  78,40,"Surely We have warned you of a doom near at hand: the day when man shall see that which his two hands have sent before, and the unbeliever shall say, \"O! Would that I were dust"
  79,1,I swear by (or call to witness) those who tear out to destruction
  79,2,And by those rushing
  79,3,And by those who float
  79,4,Then press forward as in a race
  79,5,And those who regulate affairs
  79,6,The day on which the first trump resounds (or that which can quake shall quake)
  79,7,And others follow it
  79,8,Hearts on that day shall palpitate
  79,9,While eyes are cast down
  79,10,"They say, \"Shall we indeed be restored to our first state"
  79,11,What! When we are rotten bones
  79,12,"They said, \"That then would be a return, causing loss"
  79,13,But it shall be only a single cry
  79,14,When lo! They will be fully awake
  79,15,Has not there come to you the story of Moses
  79,16,When his Lord called upon him in the holy valley of Tuwa
  79,17,"(Saying,) \"Go to Pharaoh, surely he has transgressed beyond bounds"
  79,18,"Then say, \"Have you a desire to purify yourself"
  79,19,And I will guide you to your Lord so that you may fear
  79,20,So he showed him the Mighty Sign
  79,21,But he (Pharaoh) rejected it and disobeyed
  79,22,Then turned he away (from Allah) in haste
  79,23,Then he gathered (men) and made a proclamation
  79,24,"Saying, \"I am your Lord, the most high"
  79,25,So Allah seized him with the punishment of the Hereafter and the former life
  79,26,Most surely there is in this a lesson to him who fears
  79,27,Are you the harder to create or the heaven? He created it
  79,28,"He raised high its height, and gave it order and perfection"
  79,29,And He made dark its night and its splendour does He bring out with light
  79,30,And after that He expanded (spread) the earth
  79,31,He brought forth from it its water and its pasturage
  79,32,"And the mountains, He made them firm"
  79,33,A provision for you and for your cattle
  79,34,But when the great overwhelming calamity comes
  79,35,The Day on which man shall recollect all he strove after
  79,36,And Hell shall be made manifest to him who sees
  79,37,Then for him who has transgressed all bounds
  79,38,And prefers the life of this world
  79,39,"Surely, Hell will be his abode"
  79,40,And as for him who had feared standing in the presence of his Lord and restrains his soul from lust (or low desires)
  79,41,"Then surely the Garden, that is his abode"
  79,42,"They ask you (Muhammad) about the Hour, when it will come"
  79,43,"What,\" ask they, \"have you to say about it"
  79,44,To your Lord belongs the knowledge of it
  79,45,you are only a Warner to him who would fear it
  79,46,"On the day that they behold it, it will be as though they had not tarried but an evening or the morning"
  80,1,He frowned and turned his back
  80,2,Because there came to him the blind man
  80,3,And what would make you know that he would grow (spiritually)
  80,4,Or that he might become heedful so that the reminder should profit him
  80,5,As for him who considers himself independent (or self-sufficient)
  80,6,To him do you attend
  80,7,Yet no blame is on you if he grow not (spiritually)
  80,8,And as to him who comes to you striving earnestly
  80,9,And with the fear of Allah in his heart
  80,10,From him were you unmindful (or distracted)
  80,11,"Nay! Verily, it is an admonishment (or a message of instructions)"
  80,12,So let whoever will pay heed to it
  80,13,It is in honoured books
  80,14,"Exalted, purified"
  80,15,Set down by scribes
  80,16,Noble and righteous
  80,17,Cursed (self-destroyed) is man! How ungrateful (to Allah) is he
  80,18,Of what stuff did He create him
  80,19,"Of a small seed; He created him, then gave him due proportions"
  80,20,Then He made his way easy for him
  80,21,Then He causes him to die and buries him in his grave
  80,22,"Then when He wills, He will raise him to life again"
  80,23,Nay; but man has not done that which He bade him
  80,24,Then let man consider his food
  80,25,That We pour down the water in abundance
  80,26,Then We cleave the earth
  80,27,Then We cause to grow therein the grain
  80,28,And grapes and clover
  80,29,And the olive and the palm
  80,30,And dense luxurious gardens
  80,31,And fruits and herbage
  80,32,A provision for you and for your cattle
  80,33,But when the Deafening Noise (cataclysm) comes
  80,34,The Day on which a man shall fly from his brother
  80,35,And his mother and his father
  80,36,And his spouse and his children
  80,37,Every man of them shall on that Day be occupied with concerns which will make him heedless of others
  80,38,Many faces on that Day shall be bright as dawn (or beaming with light)
  80,39,"Laughing, rejoicing"
  80,40,"And many faces on that Day, shall be covered with dust"
  80,41,Veiled in darkness
  80,42,"These are the disbelievers, the wicked"
  81,1,When the sun is overthrown (or folded up)
  81,2,And when the stars darken
  81,3,And when the mountains pass away
  81,4,And when the she-camels (with young) are left untended
  81,5,And when the wild beasts are herded together
  81,6,And when the seas swell and boil
  81,7,And when souls are sorted and reunited
  81,8,And when the female infant buried alive is asked
  81,9,For what sin she was killed
  81,10,And when the Record Books are spread open
  81,11,And when the heavens are unveiled
  81,12,And when Hell is kindled up
  81,13,And when the Garden is brought nigh
  81,14,Every soul shall then know what it has prepared
  81,15,But nay! I swear by (or call to witness) the Planets
  81,16,That run their course and hide themselves
  81,17,And the Night when it departs
  81,18,And the Dawn when it breaths away the darkness
  81,19,Most surely it is the Word of an honourable Messenger
  81,20,The possessor of power and high rank with the Lord of the Throne
  81,21,"One to be obeyed, and faithful to his trust"
  81,22,And your companion is not one possessed (or mad)
  81,23,And of a truth he saw himself on the clear horizon
  81,24,Nor is he a tenacious concealer of the unseen
  81,25,Nor is it the word of the cursed Satan
  81,26,Whither then will you go
  81,27,It is naught but a reminder unto all creation (or all the worlds)
  81,28,For him among you who wills to go straight
  81,29,"And you will not, unless Allah wills, the Lord (or Cherisher) of Creation (or all the Worlds)"
  82,1,When the heavens are cleft asunder
  82,2,And when the stars are dispersed
  82,3,And when the oceans are suffered to burst forth
  82,4,And when the graves are overturned
  82,5,Every soul shall know what it has sent before and held back
  82,6,"O man! What has beguiled you from your Lord, the Gracious one"
  82,7,"Who created you, then completed your form in due proportions, then gave you balance (or an inclination to reason and justice)"
  82,8,Into whatever form He wills He castes you
  82,9,Nay! But you deny the judgment
  82,10,And most surely there are guardians over you
  82,11,Honourable recorders
  82,12,They know what you do
  82,13,"Verily, the righteous are in bliss"
  82,14,"And verily, the wicked are in burning fire"
  82,15,They shall enter it on the Day of Judgment
  82,16,And they shall by no means be absent from it
  82,17,And what will convey unto you what the Day of Judgment is
  82,18,"Again, what will convey unto you what the Day of Judgment Is"
  82,19,The day on which no soul shall control anything for another soul; and the command on that day shall be entirely Allah´s
  83,1,Woe to the defrauders
  83,2,"Who, when they take the measure of their dues from men take it fully"
  83,3,"But when they give by measure or weight, they are deficient"
  83,4,Do not these think that they shall be raised again to account
  83,5,On a Mighty Day
  83,6,The day on which men shall stand before the Lord of the Worlds
  83,7,Nay! Most surely the record of the wicked is in Sijjin
  83,8,And what will explain to you what Sijjin is
  83,9,It is an inscribed Record
  83,10,Woe on that day to the rejecters
  83,11,Who give the lie to the Day of Judgment
  83,12,"And none deny it but the transgressors beyond bounds, the sinful one"
  83,13,"When Our revelations are recited to him, he says, \"Stories of those of yore"
  83,14,Nay! But what they used to do has become like rust upon their heart
  83,15,Nay! Most surely they shall on that day be debarred (or veiled) from their Lord
  83,16,Then most surely they shall enter the burning Fire
  83,17,"Then shall it be said, \"This is what you gave the lie to"
  83,18,Nay! Most surely the record of the righteous shall be in Iliyin
  83,19,And what will explain to you what Iliyin is
  83,20,It is an inscribed Record
  83,21,Those who are drawn near to Allah shall witness it
  83,22,Most surely the righteous shall be in bliss
  83,23,"On thrones, they shall gaze"
  83,24,You will see in their faces the brightness of bliss
  83,25,"They are given to drink pure wine, sealed"
  83,26,The sealing of it is with musk; and for that let the aspirers aspire
  83,27,And the admixture of it is a water of Tasnim
  83,28,A fountain from which drink they who are nearest to Allah
  83,29,Surely they who are guilty used to laugh at those who believe
  83,30,"And when they passed by them, they winked at one another"
  83,31,And when they returned to their own folk they returned exulting
  83,32,"And when they saw them, they said, \"Most surely these are truly astray"
  83,33,But they were not sent to be keepers over them
  83,34,This day it is the believers who shall laugh at the unbelievers
  83,35,"On thrones (of dignity), they will gaze"
  83,36,Are not the disbelievers rewarded for what they did
  84,1,When the heaven is rent asunder
  84,2,"And gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,3,And when the earth is stretched out
  84,4,"And casts forth what is within it, and is emptied (or clean)"
  84,5,"And gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,6,"O man! Verily, you are toiling on towards your Lord, painfully toiling; wherefore shall you meet Him"
  84,7,And as for him who is given his record in his right hand
  84,8,His account shall be taken with an easy reckoning
  84,9,And he shall go back to his people rejoicing
  84,10,But as for him who is given his book behind his back
  84,11,He shall call out for destruction
  84,12,But he shall broil in a blazing Fire
  84,13,"Verily, he was amongst his family joyful"
  84,14,"Verily, he thought that he should never return to Allah"
  84,15,"Nay, nay! Verily, his Lord did watch him"
  84,16,So I do call as witness the glow of sunset
  84,17,"Or the night, and its homing"
  84,18,Or the moon in her fullness
  84,19,You shall surely travel from stage to stage
  84,20,What ails them that they believe not
  84,21,"And, when the Quran is read to them, they fall not prostrate"
  84,22,"On the contrary, the unbelievers reject it"
  84,23,But Allah knows best the (malice) that they hide
  84,24,So announce to them the grievous woe
  84,25,Save those who believe and work right. For them is an unfailing reward
  85,1,By the heaven with its zodiacal signs
  85,2,And by the Promised Day
  85,3,And by the witnesses and the witnessed
  85,4,Self-destroyed were the owners of the pit
  85,5,The fire of which was supplied with abundant fuel
  85,6,"Behold, they sat over it"
  85,7,And they witnessed all they were doing against the believers
  85,8,"And they mistreated them only for their belief in Allah, the Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,Whose are the kingdoms of the heavens and the earth; for Allah is Witness over all
  85,10,"Verily, those who persecute (or mislead or tempt) the believers, men and women, and then do not repent, for them is the penalty of Hell: they will have the torment of the burning Fire"
  85,11,"Verily, those who believe and do right, for them are Gardens beneath which rivers flow: that is the great bliss"
  85,12,"Verily, strong is the power of your Lord"
  85,13,"Verily, it is He who creates and restores"
  85,14,"And He is the Forgiving, the Loving"
  85,15,The Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,The Doer of what He will
  85,17,Has there come to you the story of the Hosts
  85,18,Of Pharaoh and the Thamud
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers persist in rejecting (the truth)
  85,20,But Allah is behind them - encompassing
  85,21,"Nay, this is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,(Inscribed) in a Preserved Tablet
  86,1,By the heaven and by the night or (morning) star
  86,2,And what shall make you know what the night star is
  86,3,The star of piercing brightness
  86,4,"Verily, every soul has a guardian over it"
  86,5,Then let man look from what he is created
  86,6,He is created from a drop emitted
  86,7,Which comes out from between the loins and the breast bones
  86,8,"Surely, He is able to bring back (to life)"
  86,9,On the day when the secrets shall be tried
  86,10,And man shall have neither strength nor helper
  86,11,By the Firmament which returns in its rounds
  86,12,And the earth with its sprouting
  86,13,"Verily, this is indeed a discriminating word"
  86,14,And it is no frivolity
  86,15,"As for them, they do plot a scheme"
  86,16,But I plot my scheme too
  86,17,So give respite to the unbelievers; deal you gently with them for a while
  87,1,Glorify the name of your Guardian Lord most High
  87,2,Who created and makes order and proportion
  87,3,Who ordains Laws and Guides
  87,4,Who brings forth the pasture
  87,5,Then turns it to dusky stubble
  87,6,"We will teach you by degrees to declare (or recite), and you shall not forget"
  87,7,"Save what Allah wills. Verily, Lo! He knows the open and the hidden"
  87,8,And We will ease your way into the simple (path)
  87,9,"Therefore, remind men, for, verily, the reminder is useful"
  87,10,But he who fears will be mindful
  87,11,And the wretch will avoid it
  87,12,He will broil in the great Fire
  87,13,Wherein he shall neither die nor live
  87,14,He is successful who grows
  87,15,And remembers the name of his Lord and prays
  87,16,Nay! But you prefer the life of this world
  87,17,Although the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Verily, this was in the former books"
  87,19,The books of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,"Has the story reached you, of the overwhelming"
  88,2,Some faces on that day shall be humbled
  88,3,"Toiling, weary"
  88,4,While they broil upon a burning Fire
  88,5,While they drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,No food shall they have save from the bitter Dhari
  88,7,Which shall not nourish nor avail against hunger
  88,8,Other faces on that day shall be joyful
  88,9,Content with their past endeavours
  88,10,In a lofty (sublime) Garden
  88,11,Wherein they shall hear no foolish word
  88,12,Wherein is a flowing fountain
  88,13,Wherein are Thrones (of dignity) raised on high
  88,14,And goblets set down ready
  88,15,And cushions arranged
  88,16,And carpets spread
  88,17,"Do they not look then at the camel, how she is created"
  88,18,And at the heaven how it is raised high
  88,19,And at the mountains how they are set firm
  88,20,And at the earth how it is spread out
  88,21,"Therefore, remind them: for you are only one to remind"
  88,22,you are not in authority over them
  88,23,But such as turns his back and disbelieves
  88,24,Him will Allah punish with the greatest torment
  88,25,"Verily, unto us is their return"
  88,26,"And, verily, for Us is their accounting"
  89,1,I swear by (or call to witness) the dawn
  89,2,And by the nights twice five (of pilgrimage)
  89,3,And the even and the odd
  89,4,And the night when it passes on
  89,5,Is there not in these a lesson (evidence or admonition) for a man of understanding
  89,6,Have you not seen how your Lord did with the people of A´ad
  89,7,With the city of Iram of the lofty pillars
  89,8,The like of which has not been created in all the land
  89,9,And with the people of Thamud when they hewed the great stones in the valley
  89,10,"And with Pharaoh, Lord of the stakes"
  89,11,All these were outrageous in the land
  89,12,And did multiply wickedness therein
  89,13,"Therefore, your Lord poured out upon them the scourge of diverse torments"
  89,14,"Verily, your Lord is ever watchful"
  89,15,"Now as for man, whenever his Lord tries him and honours him and grants him favour, then he says, \"My Lord has honoured me"
  89,16,"But whenever he tries him and restricts his subsistence, then he says, \"My Lord despises me"
  89,17,"Nay, nay! But you do not honour the orphan"
  89,18,Nor do you urge each other to feed the poor
  89,19,And you devour the inheritance (of the weak) with greed
  89,20,And you love wealth with an abounding love
  89,21,"Nay, when the earth is crushed to pieces"
  89,22,"And your Lord comes with the angels, rank on rank"
  89,23,"And Hell is brought near on that Day, on that Day shall man remember! But how shall the remembrance profit him"
  89,24,"He will say, \"Would that I had sent something forward for my life"
  89,25,But on that Day none shall punish as He punishes
  89,26,And none shall be bound with bonds like his
  89,27,"But O, you soul in peace and fulfilment"
  89,28,"Return unto your Lord, well pleased and well pleasing unto Him"
  89,29,Enter you amongst My servants
  89,30,Enter you My Garden (Paradise)
  90,1,I swear (or call to witness) this City (Mecca)
  90,2,And you (Muhammad) are a dweller of this City
  90,3,And the (mystic ties) of Parent and Child
  90,4,"We have surely created man in suffering (struggle, trouble, sorrow)"
  90,5,Does he think that none has power over him
  90,6,"He says, \"I have squandered wealth in plenty"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have We not made for him two eyes
  90,9,"And a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,And guided him in the two highways
  90,11,But he has not attempted the ascent
  90,12,And what will explain to you the ascent
  90,13,"It is freeing captives (or prisoners, slaves, the restricted or bound)"
  90,14,Or feeding on the day of privation
  90,15,An orphan who is a kin
  90,16,Or a destitute lying in the dust (of misery)
  90,17,"And again (it is) to be of those who believe and encourage each other to patience, and encourage each other to mercy"
  90,18,These are the fellows of the right
  90,19,"But those who disbelieve in our signs, they are the fellows of the left"
  90,20,For them is the enclosing Fire
  91,1,By the sun and its noonday brightness
  91,2,And the moon when it follows him
  91,3,And the day when it displays him
  91,4,And the night when it covers him
  91,5,And the wondrous structure of the heavens and Him who built it
  91,6,And the earth and Who spread it
  91,7,And the soul and Who fashioned it
  91,8,And enlightened it with what is wrong and right for it
  91,9,He indeed is successful who causes it to grow (or purifies it)
  91,10,And he indeed is a failure who corrupts it
  91,11,The Thamud people denied (the Messenger) in their rebellious pride (or outrage)
  91,12,When the basest of them rose up
  91,13,"And the Messenger of Allah (Salih) said to them, \"(This is) Allah´s she-camel! So give her to drink"
  91,14,"But they called him a liar, and they ham-strung her; so their Lord destroyed them in their sins, and served them all alike"
  91,15,And He fears not the result thereof
  92,1,By the night when it veils
  92,2,And the day when it is displayed
  92,3,And by (the mystery) of male and female
  92,4,"Verily, your efforts are diverse"
  92,5,But as for him who gives alms and fears Allah
  92,6,And believes in goodness
  92,7,We will ease his way to ease
  92,8,But as for him who is niggardly and thinks himself independent (or self-sufficient)
  92,9,And calls the good a lie
  92,10,We will ease his way to misery (adversity)
  92,11,And his wealth shall not avail him when he falls down (into hell)
  92,12,"Verily, it is for Us to guide"
  92,13,"And, verily, Ours are the Latter and the Former life"
  92,14,"Therefore, I have warned you of a Fire that flames fiercely"
  92,15,"None shall broil thereon, but the most wretched"
  92,16,Who says it is a lie and turns his back
  92,17,But the pious shall be kept away from it
  92,18,He who gives his wealth that he may grow
  92,19,And who gives no favour expecting a return
  92,20,But only desiring the face of his Lord Most High
  92,21,In the end he shall be well fulfilled
  93,1,By the glorious morning light
  93,2,And the night when it is still
  93,3,"Your Lord has not forsaken you (Muhammad), nor is displeased with you"
  93,4,And surely the Hereafter is better for you than the present
  93,5,"And in the end your Lord will give you, and you shall be well pleased"
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan, and give you protection"
  93,7,"And find you wandering (or astray), and guide you"
  93,8,"And find you in need, and enriched you (or made you independent)"
  93,9,"Therefore, the orphan oppress him not"
  93,10,Nor the beggar (or petitioner) drive away
  93,11,"And as for the favour of your Lord, discourse (proclaim) thereof"
  94,1,Have We not expanded for you your breast
  94,2,And set down from you your load
  94,3,Which galled your back
  94,4,And exalted for you your renown
  94,5,"Verily, with difficulty comes ease"
  94,6,"Verily, with difficulty comes ease"
  94,7,"So when you are at relieved, then still toil"
  94,8,And to your Lord turn all your yearning (or attention)
  95,1,By the Fig and the Olive
  95,2,And by Mount Sinai
  95,3,And by this Safe City
  95,4,"Surely, We have created man in the best of moulds"
  95,5,Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,Save those who believe and act right; for theirs is a reward unfailing
  95,7,But what shall make you call the judgment after this a lie
  95,8,Is not Allah the most wise (just or conclusive) of judges
  96,1,"READ (or proclaim), in the name of your Lord! Who created"
  96,2,Created man from a clot
  96,3,"Read (or proclaim), for your Lord is most Bountiful"
  96,4,Who teaches by the pen
  96,5,Taught man what he did not know
  96,6,"Nay, verily, man is indeed rebellious"
  96,7,In that he thinks himself independent (or self-sufficient or rich)
  96,8,"Verily, unto your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Have you considered him who forbids
  96,10,A servant when he prays
  96,11,Have you considered if he were in guidance
  96,12,Or bade piety
  96,13,"Have you considered if he denied the truth, and turned his back"
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah can see
  96,15,"Nay, surely, if he does not desist, We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,The lying sinful forelock
  96,17,So let him call his council (or comrades)
  96,18,We will call the guards of Hell
  96,19,"Nay, obey him not, but adore and draw nigh (unto Allah)"
  97,1,"Verily, We sent it (the Quran) down on the Night of Power"
  97,2,And what shall make you know what the Night of Power is
  97,3,The Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"The angels and the Spirit descend therein, by the permission of their Lord with every decree"
  97,5,Peace it is until the rising of the dawn
  98,1,Those of the People of the Book and the idolaters who disbelieve did not fall away until there came to them the Manifest Sign
  98,2,A Messenger from Allah reading pure pages
  98,3,Wherein are right scriptures
  98,4,Nor did those who were given the Book divide into sects until after there came to them the Manifest Sign
  98,5,"But they were bidden nothing but to worship Allah, being sincere in religion unto Him as ´Hanifs´, and to be steadfast in prayer, and to give alms: for that is the true religion"
  98,6,"Verily, those who disbelieve amongst the people of the Book and the idolaters shall be in the fire of hell, to dwell therein for aye; they are wretched creatures"
  98,7,"Verily, those who believe and act aright, they are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord is Gardens of Eden, beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein for aye; Allah shall be well pleased with them, and they with Him! That is for him who fears his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth shall be shaken with its quaking
  99,2,And the earth shall bring forth her burdens
  99,3,"And man shall say, \"What ails her"
  99,4,On that day she shall tell her tidings
  99,5,Because your Lord inspires her
  99,6,On the day when men shall come up in separate bands to show their works
  99,7,And he who does the weight of an atom of good shall see it then
  99,8,And he who does the weight of an atom of evil shall see it
  100,1,By the snorting chargers
  100,2,And those who strike fire with their hoofs
  100,3,And those who make incursions in the morning
  100,4,And raise up dust therein
  100,5,And cleave through a host therein
  100,6,"Verily, man is to his Lord ungrateful"
  100,7,"And, verily, he is a witness of that"
  100,8,"Verily, he is keen in his love of wealth"
  100,9,Does he not know when the tombs are exposed
  100,10,And what is in the breasts is brought to light
  100,11,"Verily, your Lord upon that day indeed is well aware"
  101,1,The calamity
  101,2,What is the calamity
  101,3,And what will convey to you what the calamity is
  101,4,The day when men shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains shall be like flocks of carded wool
  101,6,And as for him whose balance is heavy
  101,7,He shall be in a well-pleasing life
  101,8,But as for him whose balance is light
  101,9,His mother will be the Bereft and Hungry One
  101,10,And who shall convey to you what she is
  101,11,A raging fire
  102,1,The rivalry in worldly increase deludes you
  102,2,Till you visit the graves
  102,3,Nay! In the end you shall know
  102,4,And again Nay! In the end you shall know
  102,5,Nay! Did you but know with certain knowledge
  102,6,You shall surely see hell
  102,7,And again you shall surely see it with an eye of certainty
  102,8,Then you shall surely be asked about pleasure
  103,1,By the declining day
  103,2,"Verily, man is in a state of loss"
  103,3,"Save those who believe and do good works, and bid each other to truth, and bid each other endurance"
  104,1,Woe to every slanderous scandal-monger and backbiter
  104,2,Who collects wealth and counts it
  104,3,He thinks that his wealth can immortalize him
  104,4,Not so! He shall be hurled into El´Hutamah
  104,5,"Ah, what shall make you understand what El´Hutamah is"
  104,6,The Fire by Allah kindled
  104,7,Which leaps into the heart
  104,8,Lo! It closes in as a vault on them
  104,9,In outstretched columns
  105,1,See you not how your Lord dealt with the people of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their stratagem lead them astray
  105,3,And sent down on them birds in flocks
  105,4,To pelt them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,And make them like stalks left by herbage eaten down
  106,1,For the taming (civilizing) of the Qureysh
  106,2,Their covenant covers their caravans in winter and summer
  106,3,So let them serve the Lord of this house
  106,4,"Who feeds them against hunger, and makes them safe against fear"
  107,1,Have you considered him who calls the judgment (or Religion) a lie
  107,2,He it is who pushes the orphan away
  107,3,And urges not (others) to feed the needy
  107,4,But woe to those who pray
  107,5,But are careless in their prayers
  107,6,Who pretend for show
  107,7,Yet withhold small kindnesses (or necessaries)
  108,1,"Verily, We have given you (Muhammad) El Kauthar (The Fountain of Abundance)"
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,"Verily, he who insults you shall be issueless (cut off)"
  109,1,"Say, \"O you faithless"
  109,2,I do not serve what you serve
  109,3,Nor will you serve what I serve
  109,4,Nor will I serve what you serve
  109,5,Nor will you serve what I serve
  109,6,To you your Way and to me my Way
  110,1,When there comes Allah´s help and victory
  110,2,And you shall see men enter into Allah´s religion in crowds
  110,3,"Then celebrate the praises of your Lord, and ask forgiveness of Him, verily, He is Relenting"
  111,1,"Perish shall the hands of The Father of Flame, and he shall perish"
  111,2,"His wealth shall not avail him, nor what he has gained"
  111,3,He shall soon broil in a Fire that flames
  111,4,And his wife shall carry the wood as fuel
  111,5,On her own neck a cord of palm fibres
  112,1,"Say, \"He is Allah, the One and Only"
  112,2,"Allah the Absolute, on whom all things depend, besought by all"
  112,3,He begets not and is not begotten
  112,4,Nor is there like unto Him any one
  113,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in the Lord of the Dawn"
  113,2,From the evil of created things
  113,3,And from the evil of the night when it cometh on
  113,4,And from the evil of those who practice secret arts
  113,5,And from the evil of the envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in the Lord and Cherisher of mankind"
  114,2,The King (or Ruler) of mankind
  114,3,The God (or Judge) of mankind
  114,4,"From the mischief of the Whisperer, who slinks off"
  114,5,Who whispers into the heart of men
  114,6,From among Jinn and Men